The paper deals with the problem of Android malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a method that combines heterogeneous information network (HIN) and deep neural network (DNN) for classification, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the construction of the HIN, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and data structures (cs.DS).
